<!-- === LINE =================================================== -->
<xsd:element name="AnnotatedLineRef" type="AnnotatedLineStructure">
<xsd:annotation>
<xsd:documentation>Information about LINEs covered by server.</xsd:documentation>
</xsd:annotation>
</xsd:element>
<xsd:complexType name="AnnotatedLineStructure">
<xsd:annotation>
<xsd:documentation>Summary information about a LINE type.</xsd:documentation>
</xsd:annotation>
<xsd:sequence>
<xsd:element name="LineRef" type="LineRefStructure">
<xsd:annotation>
<xsd:documentation>Identifier of LINE.</xsd:documentation>
</xsd:annotation>
</xsd:element>
<xsd:element maxOccurs="unbounded" name="LineName" type="NaturalLanguageStringStructure">
<xsd:annotation>
<xsd:documentation>Name of LINE. (Unbounded since SIRI 2.0)</xsd:documentation>
</xsd:annotation>
</xsd:element>
<xsd:element default="true" name="Monitored" type="xsd:boolean">
<xsd:annotation>
<xsd:documentation>
Whether the LINE has real-time info. Default is 'true'.
</xsd:documentation>
</xsd:annotation>
</xsd:element>
<xsd:element minOccurs="0" name="Destinations">
<xsd:annotation>
<xsd:documentation>
DESTINATIONs to which the LINE runs. Detail level is 'normal'
</xsd:documentation>
</xsd:annotation>
<xsd:complexType>
<xsd:sequence>
<xsd:element maxOccurs="unbounded" ref="Destination"/>
</xsd:sequence>
</xsd:complexType>
</xsd:element>
<xsd:element minOccurs="0" name="Directions">
<xsd:annotation>
<xsd:documentation>DIRECTIONs and Stops for the LINE. 'normal'</xsd:documentation>
</xsd:annotation>
<xsd:complexType>
<xsd:sequence>
<xsd:element maxOccurs="unbounded" name="Direction" type="RouteDirectionStructure">
<xsd:annotation>
<xsd:documentation>Directions of Route</xsd:documentation>
</xsd:annotation>
</xsd:element>
</xsd:sequence>
</xsd:complexType>
</xsd:element>
<xsd:element minOccurs="0" ref="Extensions"/>
</xsd:sequence>
</xsd:complexType>

<xsd:element minOccurs="0" name="JourneyPatterns">
<xsd:annotation>
<xsd:documentation>
JourneyPatterns in Direction of route (+SIRI 2.0)
</xsd:documentation>
</xsd:annotation>
<xsd:complexType>
<xsd:sequence>
<xsd:element maxOccurs="unbounded" name="JourneyPattern">
<xsd:annotation>
<xsd:documentation>JourneyPattern. (+SIRI 2.0)</xsd:documentation>
</xsd:annotation>
<xsd:complexType>
<xsd:sequence>
<xsd:element minOccurs="0" ref="JourneyPatternRef"/>
<xsd:element maxOccurs="unbounded" minOccurs="0" name="Name" type="NaturalLanguageStringStructure">
<xsd:annotation>
<xsd:documentation>Name Of Journety Pattern (SIRI 2.0)</xsd:documentation>
</xsd:annotation>
</xsd:element>
<xsd:element minOccurs="0" name="StopsInPattern">
<xsd:annotation>
<xsd:documentation>
Ordered collection of STOP POINTs the LINE and direction . Detail level is 'stops'. +SIRI v2.0
</xsd:documentation>
</xsd:annotation>
<xsd:complexType>
<xsd:sequence>
<xsd:element maxOccurs="unbounded" minOccurs="2" name="StopPointInPattern" type="StopPointInPatternStructure">
<xsd:annotation>
<xsd:documentation>
Stop within Route of LINE. Detail level is 'stop' +SIRI v2.0
</xsd:documentation>
</xsd:annotation>
</xsd:element>
</xsd:sequence>
</xsd:complexType>
</xsd:element>
</xsd:sequence>
</xsd:complexType>
</xsd:element>
</xsd:sequence>
</xsd:complexType>
</xsd:element>
<xsd:element minOccurs="0" ref="Extensions"/>
</xsd:sequence>
</xsd:extension>
</xsd:complexContent>
</xsd:complexType>
<xsd:complexType name="StopPointInPatternStructure">
<xsd:annotation>
<xsd:documentation>Summary information about a stop within line</xsd:documentation>

<xsd:sequence>
<xsd:element name="Order" type="xsd:positiveInteger">
<xsd:annotation>
<xsd:documentation>Order of STOP POINT in route +SIRI v2.0</xsd:documentation>
</xsd:annotation>
</xsd:element>
<xsd:element minOccurs="0" name="OnwardLinkShape" type="LineShapeStructure">
<xsd:annotation>
<xsd:documentation>
Plot of points from this stop to next Stop. Detail level is 'full'. +SIRI v2.0
</xsd:documentation>
</xsd:annotation>
</xsd:element>
<xsd:element minOccurs="0" name="LinkProjectionToNextStopPoint" type="ifopt:LinkProjectionStructure">
<xsd:annotation>
<xsd:documentation>
GIs projection of Link to the next provided StopPoint. NB Line here means Geometry Polyline, not Transmodel Transport Line.
</xsd:documentation>
</xsd:annotation>
</xsd:element>
<xsd:element minOccurs="0" ref="Extensions"/>
</xsd:sequence>
</xsd:extension>
</xsd:complexContent>
</xsd:complexType>

</xsd:documentation>
</xsd:annotation>
</xsd:element>

<xsd:annotation>
<xsd:documentation>
Direction in which destination lies. relatoive to currernt stop SIRI 2.0
</xsd:documentation>
</xsd:annotation>
</xsd:element>
</xsd:sequence>
